        • exportedVars2reexported

          java.util.Map<K,V> exportedVars2reexported
          map from description of variables exported by submodels that are reexported by this coupled model.

        • internalBindings

          java.util.Map<K,V> internalBindings
          bindings of variables exported by submodels to imported ones by other submodels.

        • sortedSubmodelURIs

          java.util.List<E> sortedSubmodelURIs
          URIs of the submodels that exhibit an ordering, such as a production/consumption of variables relationship, which impose an order of computation, order that is given by the list.

        • sortedSubmodels

          ModelDescriptionI[] sortedSubmodels
          the sorted submodels, in the order imposed by their relationship; all of the sorted models appear also in submodels; sortedModels and unsortedModels form a partition of submodels.

        • unsortedSubmodelURIs

          java.util.List<E> unsortedSubmodelURIs
          URIs of the submodels that do not exhibit a particular ordering relationship.

        • unsortedSubmodels

          ModelDescriptionI[] unsortedSubmodels
          the unsorted submodels in no particular order. all of the unsorted models appear also in submodels; sortedModels and unsortedModels form a partition of submodels.

        • elapsedTimes

          Duration[] elapsedTimes
          Elapsed times of submodels since their last internal event (i.e., currentStateTime; conceptually, the time of the last internal event plus the elapsed time corresponds to the current global simulation time.

        • submodelOfNextEvent

          ModelI submodelOfNextEvent
          The submodel that will need to execute the next event.

        • activeSubmodels

          java.util.Set<E> activeSubmodels
          Set of submodels that have external events waiting to be executed during the current simulation step.

        • randomGenerator

          java.util.Random randomGenerator
          Random number generator used to break the ties when several submodels can perform an internal transition at the same time of next internal transition simulation time.
